# Native libraries are committed temporarily during the cross-platform build
# to transfer them between machines via git. They are removed before the final
# squash commit (see BUILD.md Step 4). Only the JAR remains in the final
# history. Rationale: keep LFS storage small — the JAR already contains all
# three libraries, so keeping them separately would double the storage cost.
libs/*.dylib filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
libs/*.so filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
libs/*.dll filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jar filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
